                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/72½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. In a discreet manner you are to inquire whether or not, upon the
                    establishment of the Belgo-Luxemburg Economic Union in 1921, any other
                    Government, in view of an unconditional most-favored-nation clause in an
                    existing treaty with either Belgium or Luxemburg, sought to claim the advantages
                    of the union. What success attended such representation? Please report as soon
                    as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
